## FAQ: Enterprise Loan Malaysia

**Q: What's the minimum revenue to qualify for enterprise financing?**  
A: We typically work with businesses doing RM1 million+ in annual revenue. Below that, our SME facilities usually make more sense.

**Q: Can a sole proprietor apply for an enterprise loan?**  
A: Enterprise facilities are usually for Sdn Bhd companies, but we've structured facilities for larger sole proprietorships on a case-by-case basis. The business fundamentals matter more than the legal structure.

**Q: How do interest rates compare to bank loans?**  
A: We're typically 2-4% higher than standard bank rates. The tradeoff is faster approval, flexibility, and the ability to finance assets banks won't touch. For many businesses, the speed and certainty are worth more than the rate difference.

**Q: Do you finance startup enterprises?**  
A: "Startup" and "enterprise" don't usually go together. Enterprise financing assumes an established business. If you're pre-revenue, look at our SME facilities or startup-focused lenders.

**Q: Can I refinance existing equipment?**  
A: Yes, if the equipment has remaining useful life and value. Refinancing paid-off or partially paid equipment is a smart way to access capital without selling assets.

**Q: What if I've been rejected by banks?**  
A: Bank rejection isn't automatic disqualification with us. We'll look at why you were rejected. If it was collateral or speed issues, we can often help. If it was fundamental business viability concerns, that's harder.

**Q: Is there a maximum loan amount?**  
A: We handle enterprise facilities up to RM10 million. Above that, you're likely better served by corporate banking relationships or syndicated facilities.

